This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as part-of-speech (POS) tagging and named-entity (NE) recognition, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for machine translation, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) tasks. Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of named-entity recognition, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.NE).
